  "prompt": "What is meant by the hindi term 'bakchodi'?",
  "response": "'Bakchodi' is a colloquial Hindi/Urdu slang term that generally refers to:\n\n1. Idle talk or meaningless chatter\n2. Nonsensical conversation\n3. Talking without substance\n4. Bullshitting or making up stories\n5. Joking around or fooling around\n\nIt's often used informally among friends to describe unproductive or silly conversation or behavior. The term can be used both humorously and somewhat critically, depending on the context.",
